==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} < {{OF.}} < {{L.}} ''[[avunculus]]'' "mother's brother".

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#a [[brother]] of someone’s [[father]]
#a [[brother]] of someone’s [[mother]]
#a [[brother-in-law]] of someone’s [[father]]; a [[husband]] of someone’s [[paternal aunt]]
#a [[brother-in-law]] of someone’s [[mother]]; a [[husband]] of someone’s [[maternal aunt]]
#a source of advice, encouragement, or help
#(''UK informal'') A [[pawnbroker]].

